        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 2:26PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 225 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Plymouth, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plymouth, Bremen, Bourbon, Twin Lakes, and Inwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
